---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HorizontalCard from "../components/HorizontalCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Projects and Tools | Vincenzo Di Perna"
  description="Research artifacts, software tools, experimental pipelines, and work-in-progress projects by Vincenzo Di Perna."
  sideBarActiveItemID="projects"
>
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Projects and Tools</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-90">
      A selection of research artifacts, software tools, datasets, analysis
      pipelines, and exploratory projects around blockchain systems, distributed
      infrastructures, digital assets, benchmarking, reproducible experimentation,
      real-world assets, and fairer value distribution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
      <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Countering Wealth Concentration</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-warning whitespace-nowrap">Work in progress</span>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-5 opacity-80">
      Exploratory work on how blockchain systems, digital assets, incentive
      mechanisms, and decentralized infrastructures can be designed or evaluated
      to reduce excessive concentration of value, ownership, governance power,
      and access to economic opportunities.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="network-protected card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">Wealth concentration analysis toolkit</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-warning">In progress</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            A planned set of data-analysis workflows for studying concentration
            patterns in token ownership, protocol governance, and digital-asset
            ecosystems.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Token distribution</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Governance</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Analytics</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="network-protected card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">Fair value distribution models</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-warning">In progress</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Conceptual and experimental work on mechanisms that could support
            broader participation, fairer access, and less extractive forms of
            digital value creation.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Mechanism design</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Digital assets</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Economic fairness</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
      <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Real-World Assets — RWA</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-warning whitespace-nowrap">Work in progress</span>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-5 opacity-80">
      Early-stage work on the representation, evaluation, and possible
      tokenization of real-world assets within blockchain-based infrastructures,
      with attention to ownership, verification, governance, market structure,
      and practical deployment constraints.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="network-protected card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">RWA system design notes</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-warning">In progress</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            A developing research and engineering track focused on how physical
            or off-chain assets can be represented, verified, transferred, and
            governed through digital-asset infrastructures.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Asset tokenization</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Verification</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Governance</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="network-protected card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">RWA benchmarking perspective</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-warning">In progress</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            A planned evaluation angle connecting RWA platforms with system
            performance, operational assumptions, transaction costs, settlement
            behavior, and infrastructure reliability.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Benchmarking</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Settlement</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Infrastructure</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
      <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">General Experiences</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-warning whitespace-nowrap">Work in progress</span>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-5 opacity-80">
      A growing collection of practical repositories, exercises, prototypes, and
      hands-on technical experiences developed to strengthen engineering skills,
      document learning paths, and demonstrate applied work across different
      technologies.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="network-protected card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">Restaurant Solid Blockchain Prototype</h3>
<span class="badge badge-success">Available</span>
          </div>

          <p>
  A legacy MSc thesis prototype modernized into a reproducible local demo,
  combining a restaurant ordering workflow, Solid Pods concepts, mock blockchain
  payment verification, PDF bill generation, and safe Solid rebuild tooling.
</p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <a
  class="btn btn-sm btn-primary"
  href="https://github.com/vindipe/restaurant-solid-blockchain-prototype"
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
>
  Open repository
</a>

<a
  class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
  href="/research/decentralized-accounting-system"
>
  Read thesis page
</a>

            <span class="badge badge-outline">Node.js</span>
<span class="badge badge-outline">Solid Pods</span>
<span class="badge badge-outline">Mock payment</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="network-protected card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">Experimental engineering labs</h3>
            <span class="badge badge-warning">Coming soon</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Space reserved for small projects, technical experiments, and
            exploratory implementations across systems programming, backend
            development, distributed systems, blockchain tools, data workflows,
            and DevOps practices.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-4">
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Prototypes</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">Engineering practice</span>
            <span class="badge badge-outline">DevOps</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
</BaseLayout>